1b:["$","tr","6",{"className":"border-b border-[#1E3A5F]/50 hover:bg-[#162440]/50 transition-colors","children":[["$","td","0",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"A/B Testing"}],["$","td","1",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Built-in email + landing pages"}],["$","td","2",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Built-in, program-level"}],["$","td","3",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Built-in email"}]]}]
1c:["$","tr","7",{"className":"border-b border-[#1E3A5F]/50 hover:bg-[#162440]/50 transition-colors","children":[["$","td","0",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Landing Pages"}],["$","td","1",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Built-in (drag-and-drop)"}],["$","td","2",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Built-in (template-based)"}],["$","td","3",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Built-in (limited templates)"}]]}]
1d:["$","tr","8",{"className":"border-b border-[#1E3A5F]/50 hover:bg-[#162440]/50 transition-colors","children":[["$","td","0",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Starting Price"}],["$","td","1",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"$$800/mo (2K contacts)"}],["$","td","2",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"$$2,000-4,000/mo (est.)"}],["$","td","3",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"$$49/mo (1K contacts)"}]]}]
1e:["$","tr","9",{"className":"border-b border-[#1E3A5F]/50 hover:bg-[#162440]/50 transition-colors","children":[["$","td","0",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Ease of Use"}],["$","td","1",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐"}],["$","td","2",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"⭐⭐⭐"}],["$","td","3",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐"}]]}]
1f:["$","h2","21",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"HubSpot Marketing Hub (G2 Rating: 4.4/5)"}]
20:["$","p","23",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Best for:"}]," Mid-market companies wanting integrated CRM + marketing automation in one platform."]}]
21:["$","p","25",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["HubSpot's marketing automation is deeply integrated with its CRM, making it the strongest choice for companies that want sales and marketing on the same platform. The visual campaign builder lets marketers design complex workflows without coding."]}]
22:["$","p","27",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"What I like:"}]," The CRM integration is the headline feature. When a lead fills out a form, their entire contact record updates — including sales activities, email engagement, and website visits — in real time. G2 users rate HubSpot 91% for ease of use. One reviewer from a mid-market SaaS company said: \"HubSpot cut our lead-to-meeting time by 40% because sales can see exactly what marketing content each lead has engaged with.\""]}]
23:["$","p","29",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"What I don't like:"}]," The cost escalates quickly. Marketing Hub Professional starts at $800/month for 2,000 contacts, and adding multiple contact tiers can push costs to $3,000-6,000/month. According to G2 reviews, advanced reporting requires the Enterprise plan ($3,600+/month), which is a significant jump."]}]
24:["$","p","31",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Real user feedback:"}]," Capterra rates HubSpot 4.4/5, with users praising its template library and analytics dashboard. Common complaints include the cost of add-on hubs and the learning curve for advanced automation workflows."]}]
25:["$","p","33",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Best for scaling:"}]," Teams that want marketing and sales on the same platform, with room to grow into CMS and service hubs."]}]
26:["$","p","35",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Pricing:"}]," Free CRM; Starter $45/month (1K contacts); Professional $800/month (2K contacts); Enterprise $3,600/month (10K contacts)."]}]
27:["$","h2","37",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"Marketo Engage (G2 Rating: 4.1/5)"}]
28:["$","p","39",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Best for:"}]," Large enterprises with complex, multi-channel marketing operations."]}]
29:["$","p","41",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["Marketo (now part of Adobe Experience Cloud) is the enterprise standard for B2B marketing automation. Its strength is sophisticated lead management, including dynamic segmentation, predictive scoring, and multi-touch attribution."]}]
2a:["$","p","43",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"What I like:"}]," Marketo's engagement engine can handle millions of contacts with deeply personalized journeys. The predictive scoring (powered by Adobe Sensei AI) identifies which leads are most likely to convert, and the program-level analytics give granular ROI visibility. According to G2 reviews, enterprise users rate Marketo 90% for advanced segmentation and lead management capabilities."]}]
2b:["$","p","45",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"What I don't like:"}]," The learning curve is significant. G2 reviews consistently note that Marketo requires dedicated expertise. One reviewer from a Fortune 500 company said: \"Marketo is incredibly powerful, but we have a team of three full-time Marketo admins.\" The pricing is opaque and typically starts at $2,000-4,000/month, escalating quickly with contact volume."]}]
2c:["$","p","47",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Real user feedback:"}]," Capterra reviews (4.0/5) highlight Marketo's scalability and depth, but note that \"you need a specialist to get real value.\" The Adobe acquisition has created uncertainty — some users report feature overlap and integration challenges with other Adobe products."]}]
2d:["$","p","49",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Pricing:"}]," Custom-quoted; expect $2,000-4,000/month for mid-market deployments. Enterprise deployments with full Adobe Experience Cloud integration can cost $20,000+/month."]}]
2e:["$","h2","51",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"ActiveCampaign (G2 Rating: 4.5/5)"}]
2f:["$","p","53",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Best for:"}]," Small to mid-size businesses wanting powerful automation without enterprise pricing or complexity."]}]
30:["$","p","55",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["ActiveCampaign combines email marketing, marketing automation, and CRM in an affordable, intuitive package. Its automation builder offers conditional logic, split paths, and goal-based triggers."]}]
31:["$","p","57",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"What I like:"}]," The value proposition is unbeatable. For $49/month (1,000 contacts, Plus plan), you get advanced automation that would cost 10x more with HubSpot or Marketo. G2 users rate ActiveCampaign 4.5/5, with particular praise for its automation builder (rated 93% for ease of use). One reviewer said: \"ActiveCampaign's automation is as powerful as platforms costing 10x more — the interface just makes it easier to build.\""]}]
32:["$","p","59",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"What I don't like:"}]," ActiveCampaign's CRM is functional but not as deep as HubSpot's. Reporting and analytics are good but lack the depth of Marketo's program-level ROI analysis. For very large contact databases (500K+), performance can lag."]}]
33:["$","p","61",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Real user feedback:"}]," Capterra reviewers (4.5/5) consistently praise ActiveCampaign's value for money. The predictive sending feature — which analyzes when individual contacts are most likely to engage — is a standout. Some users note that template customization is less flexible than HubSpot."]}]
34:["$","p","63",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Pricing:"}]," Plus $49/month (1K contacts); Professional $79/month (1K contacts); Enterprise $145/month (1K contacts). Scales up based on contact volume."]}]
35:["$","h2","65",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"Features Deep Dive"}]
36:["$","h3","67",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"Email Automation & Workflows"}]
37:["$","p","69",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["HubSpot offers the most polished visual builder, with conditional branching, delay actions, goal-based triggers, and internal notification steps. Marketo's Smart Campaigns are more powerful but less intuitive — they use a trigger/filter/flow model that requires training. ActiveCampaign's automation builder is closest to HubSpot in ease of use, with a clean drag-and-drop interface and excellent conditional logic."]}]
38:["$","p","71",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Winner: HubSpot"}]," (for ease) and ",["$","strong","3",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Marketo"}]," (for depth) — ActiveCampaign is a close second to HubSpot on ease."]}]
39:["$","h3","73",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"Lead Scoring"}]
3a:["$","p","75",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["HubSpot uses a simple point-based system (implicit + explicit scoring) that's easy to set up. Marketo's predictive scoring (Adobe Sensei) is the most sophisticated — it automatically identifies patterns that correlate with conversion. ActiveCampaign offers conditional scoring that's more basic but functional."]}]
3b:["$","p","77",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Winner: Marketo"}]," — the AI-powered predictive scoring is genuinely differentiating for enterprises with large lead databases."]}]
3c:["$","h3","79",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"Segmentation"}]
3d:["$","p","81",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["All three platforms offer robust segmentation, but Marketo's dynamic lists and smart campaigns provide the most granular control. HubSpot's list-based segmentation is intuitive but less flexible for complex conditions. ActiveCampaign's tags + custom fields approach is simple but can become unwieldy at scale."]}]
3e:["$","p","83",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Winner: Marketo"}]," for enterprise-scale segmentation; ",["$","strong","3",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"HubSpot"}]," for ease of use."]}]
3f:["$","h3","85",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"Analytics & Reporting"}]
40:["$","p","87",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["HubSpot provides excellent campaign-level analytics with attribution reporting (single-touch and multi-touch). Marketo's Program ROI analysis is the gold standard for B2B — you can attribute revenue to specific programs and channels. ActiveCampaign's reporting is solid but lacks the depth for enterprise marketing operations."]}]
41:["$","p","89",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Winner: Marketo"}]," — the ROI reporting capabilities are unmatched."]}]
42:["$","h2","91",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"Which Should You Choose?"}]
43:["$","p","93",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Choose HubSpot Marketing Hub if:"}]," You need an all-in-one platform where marketing, sales, and service share the same data. You're a mid-market company (50-500 employees) with budget for the premium pricing."]}]
44:["$","p","95",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Choose Marketo Engage if:"}]," You're an enterprise (1,000+ employees) with complex marketing operations, dedicated marketing automation specialists, and budget for enterprise pricing. You need predictive lead scoring and multi-touch attribution."]}]
45:["$","p","97",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Choose ActiveCampaign if:"}]," You're a small to mid-size business (10-200 employees) that needs sophisticated marketing automation but can't justify HubSpot or Marketo pricing. You want the best value-for-money in the market."]}]
46:["$","h3","99",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"My Personal Take"}]
47:["$","p","101",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["For most B2B companies, I'd start with ActiveCampaign. The feature set covers 90% of what teams need at 10-20% of the cost. As you grow into the mid-market ($5M+ ARR), HubSpot becomes the natural upgrade path for its integrated CRM. Marketo only makes sense for large enterprises that have outgrown HubSpot or need Adobe ecosystem integration."]}]
48:["$","p","103",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["*Sources: G2 Marketing Automation Grid Report (Spring 2026), Capterra Marketing Automation Reviews (2026), TrustRadius verified reviews (2026). Pricing from official vendor websites as of May 2026.*"]}]
